** formal

Wikipedia lists other things that are not strictly math as formal science,

- Formal logic
- Theoretical computer science
- Game theory
- Decision theory
- Actuarial science
- Information theory
- Systems theory
- Control theory

Also there is mathematical statistics which is an application of
probability theory In the current hierarchy everything is under math.
To be challenged later. Maybe splits formal science into multiple
fields of math.
